"349","<BODY STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif>"
"350","<P STYLE=margin: 0>[LOGO APPEARS HERE]</P>"
"351","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0><B>&nbsp;</B></P>"
"352","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center; color: #1A1A1A><B>REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED"
"353","PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</B></P>"
"354","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center>&nbsp;</P>"
"355","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A><B>To the Board of Trustees"
"356","of Papp Investment Trust</B></P>"
"357","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A><B>and the Shareholders of"
"358","Papp Small &amp; Mid-Cap Growth Fund</B></P>"
"359","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A><B>&nbsp;</B></P>"
"360","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>In planning and performing"
"361","our audit of the financial statements of Papp Small &amp; Mid-Cap Growth Fund, a series of shares of beneficial interest in Papp"
"362","Investment Trust (the <B><I>&ldquo;Fund&rdquo;</I></B>), as of November 30, 2019, and for the year then ended, in accordance with"
"363","the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States) (<B><I>&ldquo;PCAOB&rdquo;</I></B>), we considered"
"364","the Fund&rsquo;s internal control over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing"
"365","our auditing procedures for the purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the requirements"
"366","of Form N-CEN, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Fund&rsquo;s internal control over"
"367","financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion.</P>"
"368","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>&nbsp;</P>"
"369","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>The management of the Fund"
"370","is responsible for establishing and maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility,"
"371","estimates and judgments by management are required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of controls. A fund&rsquo;s"
"372","internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial"
"373","reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with accounting principles generally"
"374","accepted in the United States of America (<B><I>&ldquo;GAAP&rdquo;</I></B>). A fund&rsquo;s internal control over financial reporting"
"375","includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and"
"376","fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions"
"377","are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of the financial statements in accordance with GAAP, and that receipts and expenditures"
"378","of the fund are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and Trustees of the fund; and (3) provide reasonable"
"379","assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of a fund&rsquo;s assets that"
"380","could have a material effect on the financial statements.</P>"
"381","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>&nbsp;</P>"
"382","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>Because of inherent limitations,"
"383","internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness"
"384","to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions or that the degree"
"385","of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.</P>"
"386","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>&nbsp;</P>"
"387","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>A deficiency in internal control"
"388","over financial reporting exists when the design or operation of a control does not allow management or employees, in the normal"
"389","course of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency,"
"390","or combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that"
"391","a material misstatement of the Fund&rsquo;s annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely"
"392","basis.</P>"
"393","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>&nbsp;</P>"
"394","<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 1 -->"
"395","    <DIV STYLE=margin-bottom: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"396","    <DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"397","    <!-- Field: /Page -->"
"398","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A></P>"
"399","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; color: #1A1A1A>Our consideration of the Fund&rsquo;s"
"400","internal control over financial reporting was for the limited purpose described in the first paragraph and would not necessarily"
"401","disclose all deficiencies in internal control that might be material weaknesses under standards established by the PCAOB. However,"
